@page "/faq"

<PageTitle>
    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Title">
        Frequently Asked Questions
    </LocalizedText>
</PageTitle>

<div class="container-xxl">
    <div class="bg-light p-5 rounded shadow mb-4">
        <h1>
            <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Title">
                Frequently Asked Questions
            </LocalizedText>
        </h1>
        <p class="lead">
            <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Subtitle">
                Find answers to common questions about our localization portal.
            </LocalizedText>
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion"
         id="faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#faq1"
                        aria-expanded="true"
                        aria-controls="faq1">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Question1">
                        What is the Localization Portal?
                    </LocalizedText>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq1"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
                 data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Answer1">
                        The Localization Portal is a centralized platform for managing translations and content across
                        multiple languages and cultures. It allows you to efficiently organize, translate, and maintain
                        your application's text content in different languages.
                    </LocalizedText>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#faq2"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="faq2">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Question2">
                        How do I add a new language?
                    </LocalizedText>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq2"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Answer2">
                        To add a new language, navigate to the Culture settings in the administration panel. Click "Add
                        Culture" and select the desired language from the dropdown. Once added, you can begin
                        translating content for that culture.
                    </LocalizedText>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#faq3"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="faq3">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Question3">
                        What content types can be localized?
                    </LocalizedText>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq3"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Answer3">
                        You can localize various content types including:
                        <ul class="mt-2">
                            <li>UI text and labels</li>
                            <li>Error messages and notifications</li>
                            <li>Page content and descriptions</li>
                            <li>Email templates</li>
                            <li>Help documentation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </LocalizedText>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#faq4"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="faq4">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Question4">
                        How are themes related to localization?
                    </LocalizedText>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq4"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Answer4">
                        Themes allow you to organize your content into logical groups or categories. Each theme can have
                        its own set of localized content, making it easier to manage translations for different sections
                        of your application or different products.
                    </LocalizedText>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#faq5"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="faq5">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Question5">
                        Can I export and import translations?
                    </LocalizedText>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq5"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Answer5">
                        Yes, the portal supports exporting translations to common formats like JSON, XML, or RESX files.
                        This allows you to work with external translation services or share translations between
                        different environments. Imports can be performed to bulk-update translations.
                    </LocalizedText>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#faq6"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="faq6">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Question6">
                        What happens if a translation is missing?
                    </LocalizedText>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq6"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Answer6">
                        When a translation is missing for a specific culture, the system will fall back to the default
                        language (typically English). This ensures your application always displays some content, even
                        if translations are incomplete. Missing translations are typically logged so they can be
                        identified and addressed.
                    </LocalizedText>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                        type="button"
                        data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#faq7"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        aria-controls="faq7">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Question7">
                        How do I get support?
                    </LocalizedText>
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq7"
                 class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                 data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <LocalizedText Key="@Localizations.Faq.Answer7">
                        For technical support, please contact our support team at <a
                           href="mailto:support@example.com">support@example.com</a>. You can also check our
                        documentation or submit a ticket through the help portal for assistance with specific issues.
                    </LocalizedText>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>